  {
    "lesson_id": "055",
    "trigger_word": "antaŭjuĝo",
    "title": "LESSON 55: THE 'FI-' PREFIX",
    "header_color": "green",
    "pages": [
      {
        "page": 1,
        "total_pages": 1,
        "content": [
          "The prefix FI- means \"shameful,\" \"morally",
          "bad,\" or \"disgusting.\" It adds contempt.",
          "",
          "MORALLY BAD:",
          "homo    → fihomo      = person → scoundrel",
          "vorto   → fivorto     = word → swear word",
          "ago     → fiago       = act → shameful act",
          "fama    → fifama      = famous → infamous",
          "",
          "AS INTERJECTION: Fi! = Shame! Fie!",
          "",
          "COMPARE WITH MAL-:",
          "mal- = opposite (malbona = bad)",
          "fi-  = morally bad/shameful (fia = shameful)",
          "",
          "IN USE:",
          "Ne uzu fivortojn!",
          "(Don't use swear words!)"
        ],
        "pronunciation": "Leciono kvindek kvin"
      }
    ]
  },
